#, c-format
msgid "Imam %s"
msgstr "Imam %s"

#: data/nation/indonesian.ruleset:22
#, c-format
msgid "Imama %s"
msgstr "Imama %s"

#: data/nation/iroquois.ruleset:5
msgid "Iroquois"
msgstr "irokesisch"

#: data/nation/iroquois.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Iroquois"
msgstr "Irokesen"

#: data/nation/iroquois.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Iroquois Confederacy - known as Haudenosaunee in their own language - "
"was a North American group of nations with common language and culture. They "
"were based in what is now upstate New York and consisted originally of five "
"nations: Seneca, Cayuga, Onondaga, Oneida and Mohawk. The confederacy had a "
"written constitution and a currency system making them the most advanced "
"state in North America upon the arrival of the Europeans."
msgstr ""
"Die Irokesische Konföderation - in ihrer eigenen Sprache Haudenosaunee - war "
"eine nordamerikanische Gruppe von Nationen mit gemeinsamer Sprache und "
"Kultur. Ihr Zentrum war das nördliche Hinterland des heutigen Bundesstaates "
"New York und bestand ursprünglich aus fünf Nationen: Seneca, Cayuga, "
"Onondaga, Oneida und Mohawk. Die Konföderation besaß eine geschriebene "
"Verfassung und ein Währungssystem, wodurch sie die fortschrittlichste Nation "
"in Nordamerika bis zum Eintreffen der Europäer waren."

#: data/nation/italian.ruleset:5
msgid "Italian"
msgstr "italienisch"

#: data/nation/italian.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Italians"
msgstr "Italiener"

#: data/nation/italian.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Italian nation was unified in 1870 CE after decades of campaigning by "
"indigenous nationalists. It was a monarchy under the House of Savoy until "
"1922, then a fascist state until 1945 after which democracy was restored by "
"the World War II victors."
msgstr ""
"Italien vereinigte sich 1870 nach Jahrzehnten von Ränkekämpfen. Bis 1922 war "
"es eine Monarchie unter dem Königshaus der Savoyer, danach ein "
"faschistischer Staat bis 1945, als von den Siegern des zweiten Weltkrieges "
"eine Demokratie errichtet wurde."

#: data/nation/italian.ruleset:43
#, c-format
msgid "Duce %s"
msgstr "Duce %s"

#: data/nation/italian.ruleset:43
#, c-format
msgid "Ducezza %s"
msgstr "Ducezza %s"

#: data/nation/japanese.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"According to traditional Japanese mythology, Japan was founded in the 7th "
"century BCE by the ancestral Emperor Jimmu."
msgstr ""
"Nach der traditionellen japanischen Mythologie wurde Japan im 7. Jahrhundert "
"v. Chr. von Kaiser Jimmu gegründet."

#: data/nation/khmer.ruleset:5
msgid "Khmer"
msgstr "khmerisch"

#: data/nation/khmer.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Khmers"
msgstr "Khmer"

#: data/nation/khmer.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Khmer Empire, established in 802 CE, dominated Southeast Asia for many "
"centuries during the Middle Ages. Heavily influenced by Indian culture, the "
"Khmers were great builders who erected innumerable stone temples to Hindu "
"deities. The Khmers today are the majority ethnicity of Cambodia."
msgstr ""
"Das Khmer-Reich wurde 802 u.Z. gegründet und dominierte Südostasien für "
"viele Jahrhunderte des Mittelalters. Sie unterlagen einem starken Einfluss "
"durch die indische Kultur und hervorragende Baumeister, die zahllose "
"hinduistische Steintempel errichteten. Khmer stellen heute den größten Teil "
"der kambodschanischen Bevölkerung."

#: data/nation/korean.ruleset:5
msgid "Korean"
msgstr "koreanisch"

#: data/nation/korean.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Koreans"
msgstr "Koreaner"

#: data/nation/korean.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"According to legend, the first Korean kingdom was founded in prehistory by "
"the ancestral Tangun in southern Manchuria. The Korean kingdoms were united "
"in 668 by king Munmu. Today the Korean peninsula is divided into two states, "
"North and South Korea, as a result of the stalemate after the Korean war in "
"1953."
msgstr ""
"Nach der Legende wurde das erste koreanische Königreich in "
"vorgeschichtlicher Zeit von Tangun in der südlichen Mandschurei gegründet. "
"668 wurden die koreanischen Königreiche von König Munmu geeint. Heute ist "
"die koreanische Halbinsel in zwei Staaten geteilt, Nord- und Südkorea "
"entstanden als ein Ergebnis des militärischen Patts nach dem Koreakrieg 1953."

# CK: Originalform, Bedeutung: Königin
#: data/nation/mali.ruleset:5
msgid "Mali"
msgstr "malinkisch"

#: data/nation/mali.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Malis"
msgstr "Malinke"

#: data/nation/mali.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Sub-Saharan Africa has been a cultural and ethnical melting pot for "
"millennia. In medieval times, the region was home to a succession of empires "
"called the Sahelian kingdoms. Of these, the Islamic Mali Empire was the most "
"influential. This empire reigned from the 14th to the 17th century and was "
"famed for its wealth and benevolent kings. The modern Republic of Mali "
"derives its name from this empire."
msgstr ""
"Das Afrika südlich der Sahara ist seit Jahrtausenden ein kultureller und "
"ethnischer Schmelztiegel. Im Mittelalter gab es dort verschiedene "
"Königreiche. Eines davon, das islamische Großreich Mali mit der Hauptstadt "
"Timbuktu, war das einflussreichste. Es herrschte vom 14. bis 17. Jahrhundert "
"und war berühmt für seine wohlhabenden und wohlwollenden Könige. Die heutige "
"Republik Mali hat hiervon seinen Namen abgeleitet."

#. TRANS: Mansa = King of kings
#: data/nation/mali.ruleset:28 data/nation/songhai.ruleset:27
#, c-format
msgid "Mansa %s"
msgstr "Mansa %s"

#: data/nation/mali.ruleset:28 data/nation/songhai.ruleset:27
#, c-format
msgid "?female:Mansa %s"
msgstr "Mansa %s"

#: data/nation/mayan.ruleset:5
msgid "Mayan"
msgstr "mayaisch"

#: data/nation/mayan.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Mayas"
msgstr "Maya"

#: data/nation/mayan.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Mayans were a Mesoamerican civilization. They are famous for building "
"great pyramids and palaces in the jungle."
msgstr ""
"Die Maya waren eine mesoamerikanische Zivilisation. Bekannt sind die großen "
"Pyramiden und Paläste, die sie im Dschungel errichteten."

#: data/nation/persian.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The first Persian (Achaemenid) Empire lasted from 550 BCE to 330 BCE; the "
"second (Sassanid) from 226 CE to 642 CE."
msgstr ""
"Das erste persische (achämenidische) Reich existierte von 330-55  v.u.Z.; "
"das zweite (sassanidische) Reich von 226-642 u.Z."

#: data/nation/persian.ruleset:24
#, c-format
msgid "Satrap %s"
msgstr "Satrap %s"

#: data/nation/persian.ruleset:24
#, c-format
msgid "?female:Satrap %s"
msgstr "Satrapin %s"

#: data/nation/polish.ruleset:5
msgid "Polish"
msgstr "polnisch"

#: data/nation/polish.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Poles"
msgstr "Polen"

#: data/nation/polish.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Polish state was formed about a millennium ago, and reached its Golden "
"Age near the end of the 16th century."
msgstr ""
"Der polnische Staat wurde vor über einem Jahrtausend gebildet und erreichte "
"seine goldene Zeit am Ende des 16. Jahrhunderts."

#: data/nation/polynesian.ruleset:5
msgid "Polynesian"
msgstr "polynesisch"

#: data/nation/polynesian.ruleset:6
#, fuzzy
msgid "?plural:Polynesians"
msgstr "Polynesier"

#: data/nation/polynesian.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Polynesian culture stretches from Hawaii to New Zealand to Easter Island and "
"covers all the islands in between."
msgstr ""
"Die polynesische Kultur erstreckt sich von Hawai’i über Neuseeland bis hin "
"zu den Osterinseln und ist auf all den Inseln dazwischen präsent."

#: data/nation/portuguese.ruleset:5
msgid "Portuguese"
msgstr "portugiesisch"

#: data/nation/portuguese.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Portuguese"
msgstr "Portugiesen"

#: data/nation/portuguese.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Portugal founded the first of the great mercantile empires in the 1400s on "
"the shipbuilding advances funded by Prince Henry the Navigator."
msgstr ""
"Portugal gründete das erste große Handelsreich im 15. Jahrhundert auf seinen "
"Vorsprung im Schiffsbau, durch Prinz Heinrich der Navigator."

#: data/nation/portuguese.ruleset:28
#, c-format
msgid "Viscount %s"
msgstr "Vicomte %s"

# ?
#: data/nation/portuguese.ruleset:28
#, c-format
msgid "Viscountess %s"
msgstr "Vicomte %s"

#: data/nation/roman.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Rome was, in legend, founded by Romulus in 753 BCE. At its height, Rome "
"controlled much of Europe, northern Africa and the Near East. Roman culture "
"adopted much of the civilizations it conquered, such as the Greeks and "
"Etruscans, and forms one of the bases of the Western culture. Even today, "
"Roman influence in fields such as law, philosophy and language remains "
"enormous. The Roman civilization spanned more than a millennium; first as a "
"kingdom, later as a republic and then from 27 BCE onward as an empire. The "
"empire was split in the 4th century CE. The Western Roman Empire fell in 476 "
"CE, the Eastern Roman or Byzantine Empire survived almost a thousand years "
"more; its capital Constantinople fell to the Turks in 1453."
msgstr ""
"Der Legende nach wurde Rom durch Romulus im Jahre 753 v.u.Z. gegründet. Auf "
"der Höhe seiner Macht kontrollierte Rom große Teile Europas, Nordafrikas und "
"des Nahen Ostens, die römische Kultur unterlag dabei zahlreichen Einflüssen "
"der eroberten Zivilisationen, unter denen etwa die Griechen und Etrusker "
"waren. Sie formte den Grundstein der westlichen Kultur und noch heute ist "
"der römische Einfluss auf Recht, Philosophie und Sprache nicht zu übersehen. "
"Insgesamt umspannte die römische Zivilisation mehr als ein Jahrtausend: "
"Zunächst als Königreich, später als Republik und seit 27 u.Z. schließlich "
"als Kaiserreich. Im 4.Jh. u.Z. wurde das römische Kaiserreich aufgespalten; "
"das westliche Rom fiel 476, wohingegen Ostrom, bekannt unter dem Namen des "
"byzantinischen Imperiums, fast ein weiteres Jahrtausend länger überlebte. "
"Ihre Hauptstadt Konstantinopel fiel erst 1453 in die Hände der Türken."

#: data/nation/roman.ruleset:50
#, c-format
msgid "Tribune %s"
msgstr "Tribun %s"

#: data/nation/roman.ruleset:50
#, c-format
msgid "?female:Tribune %s"
msgstr "Tribunin %s"

#: data/nation/roman.ruleset:52
#, c-format
msgid "%s Augustus"
msgstr "%s Augustus"

#: data/nation/roman.ruleset:52
#, c-format
msgid "%s Augusta"
msgstr "%s Augusta"

#: data/nation/russian.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Russia is the largest country in the world, occupying a huge part of both "
"Europe and Asia. According to legend, Slavic tribes of Novgorod invited the "
"Varangian (Viking) king Oleg to bring order to their land. Oleg established "
"the Kievan Rus' in this realm, the first Russian state. By the 11th century, "
"the Kievan Rus' had disintegrated into lesser princedoms, which were once "
"again united into one state by Ivan III in the 15th century. After a "
"decisive victory over Sweden and large territorial gains, Peter I pronounced "
"the Russian Empire in 1721. The Russian Empire lasted until 1917 when a "
"socialist revolution dethroned the last Russian emperor. After the "
"dissolution of the USSR in 1991 Russia appeared on the world map again, now "
"as a federal republic."
msgstr ""
"Nach der Legende luden slawische und finnische Stämme 862 den Wikingerkönig "
"Rurik ein, Ordnung in ihr Land zu bringen. Rurik gründete die Kiewer Rus, "
"den ersten russischen Staat. Im 11. Jahrhundert hatte sich die Kiewer Rus in "
"kleinere Fürstentümer aufgelöst, die im 15. Jahrhundert noch einmal von Ivan "
"III. in einem Staat vereinigt wurden. Nach seinem entscheidenden Sieg über "
"Schweden und großen Landgewinnen rief Peter I. 1721 das Russische Reich aus. "
"Das Russische Reich bestand bis 1917, als eine sozialistische Revolution den "
"letzten russischen Kaiser entthronisierte. Nach Auflösung der UdSSR erschien "
"Russland 1991 erneut auf der Weltkarte, dieses Mal als föderale Republik."

#: data/nation/sioux.ruleset:32 data/nation/tupi.ruleset:26
#, c-format
msgid "Shaman %s"
msgstr "Schamane %s"

#: data/nation/sioux.ruleset:32 data/nation/tupi.ruleset:26
#, c-format
msgid "?female:Shaman %s"
msgstr "Schamanin %s"

#: data/nation/songhai.ruleset:5
msgid "Songhai"
msgstr "songhaianisch"

#: data/nation/songhai.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Songhai"
msgstr "Songhai"

#: data/nation/songhai.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Songhai people established a state in the 11th century CE centered on "
"the city of Gao. Following the decline of the Mali empire a few hundred "
"years later, the Songhai established an empire of their own which eventually "
"grew to become one of the largest in the history of Africa. The rulers of "
"Songhai became known for their wealth as well as their devotion to the "
"Muslim faith."
msgstr ""
"Die Songhai errichteten im 11. Jh u.Z. ein Reich mit der Hauptstadt Gao. "
"Nach dem Fall des malinkischen Imperiums einige hundert Jahre später "
"etablierten die Songhai ihr eigenes Imperium, das schließlich zu dem größten "
"der afrikanischen Geschichte heranwuchs. Ihre Herrscher waren sowohl für "
"ihren wohlhabenden Lebensstil als auch für ihre Hingabe an den islamischen "
"Glauben bekannt."

#: data/nation/sumerian.ruleset:5
msgid "Sumerian"
msgstr "sumerisch"

#: data/nation/sumerian.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Sumerians"
msgstr "Sumerer"

#: data/nation/sumerian.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Sumer controlled southern Mesopotamia until the rise of Babylonia. Tablets "
"of Sumerian writing some 5500 years old have been found, pre-dating every "
"other writing in history."
msgstr ""
"Die Sumerer kontrollierten das südliche Mesopotamien bis zum Aufstieg "
"Babylons. Die ältesten gefundenen Tafeln mit sumerischer Schrift sind etwa "
"5550 Jahre alt, älter als jedes andere schriftliche Zeugnis der Geschichte."

#: data/nation/swedish.ruleset:5
msgid "Swedish"
msgstr "schwedisch"

#: data/nation/swedish.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Swedes"
msgstr "Schweden"

#: data/nation/swedish.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Kingdom of Sweden was christianized and consolidated as a political "
"entity by the 12th century CE. The country rose to prominence as one of the "
"great powers of Europe in the 17th century, following substantial military "
"conquests by the so called Warrior Kings. However, due to a worsening "
"economy and several disastrous defeats to Russia, Sweden soon lost most of "
"its gained territory. The country has not been involved in an armed conflict "
"since 1814."
msgstr ""
"Das Königreich Schweden wurde im 12. Jahrhundert christianisiert und als "
"politische Einheit konsolidiert. Das Land wurde eines der größten Mächte "
"Europas im 17. Jahrhundert, vorausgegangen waren wichtige militärische "
"Eroberungen durch die sogenannten Kriegskönige. Durch eine schlechtere "
"Wirtschaft und mehrere vernichtende Niederlagen gegen Russland verlor "
"Schweden jedoch die meisten seiner errungenen Gebiete. Das Land ist seit "
"1814 nicht mehr an einem bewaffneten Konflikt beteiligt gewesen."

#: data/nation/taino.ruleset:5
msgid "Taino"
msgstr "taínoisch"

#: data/nation/taino.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Taino"
msgstr "Taíno"

# MG: Die im Deutschen nicht verwendeten Wörter wie „potato“ habe ich
# gemäß den unter https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ta%C3%ADno aufgeführten
# ersetzt.
#: data/nation/taino.ruleset:9
msgid ""
"Native inhabitants of the Bahamas, Cuba, Hispaniola, Puerto Rico, Jamaica, "
"and other Caribbean islands who gave us the root words for hurricane, "
"tobacco, potato, canoe, barbeque, hammock, and yucca. They were a "
"matrilineal people, and the first that Columbus came into contact with in "
"1492. Though numbering the hundreds of thousands, if not millions, "
"throughout the Caribbean, the Taino fell victim to slavery and disease, and "
"their population declined rapidly as a result. Spanish accounts paint them "
"as a peaceful people compared to their Carib neighbors to the south. Their "
"dugout canoes, which were often nearly as long as Columbus' ships, ferried "
"traders between islands. Recent genetic studies show that roughly half of "
"Puerto Ricans have Taino maternal descent."
msgstr ""
"Die Ureinwohner der Bahamas, Kubas, Hispaniolas, Puerto Ricos, Jamaicas und "
"anderer karibischer Inseln gaben uns die Wortwurzeln für den Hurrikan, "
"Ananas, Tabak, Kanu, Barbecue, Kaiman und Yukka. Sie waren ein matrilineares "
"Volk und darüber hinaus das erste, mit dem Kolumbus 1492 in Kontakt trat. "
"Obwohl sie insgesamt hunderttausende zählten, wenn nicht gar Millionen, "
"fielen sie in der gesamten Karibik der Sklaverei und Seuchen zum Opfer, "
"sodass im Ergebnis ihre Anzahl drastisch reduziert wurde. Die Spanier sahen "
"sie als im Vergleich mit ihren südlicheren karibischen Nachbarn recht "
"friedliches Volk an. Ihre Einbäume, häufig fast genauso lang wie Kolumbus’ "
"Schiffe, transportierten Händler zwischen den einzelnen Inseln; jüngste "
"genetische Studien legen zudem nahe, dass gut die Hälfte der Einwohner "
"Puerto Ricos mütterlicherseits Taíno als Vorfahren haben."

#: data/nation/thai.ruleset:5
msgid "Thai"
msgstr "thailändisch"

#: data/nation/thai.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Thai"
msgstr "Thailänder"

#: data/nation/thai.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Thai kingdom was the only country in Southeast Asia to preserve its "
"independence through the colonial era of the 18th and 19th centuries CE."
msgstr ""
"Thailand war der einzige Staat Südostasiens, der während der Kolonialära im "
"18. und 19. Jahrhundert seine Unabhängigkeit bewahrte."

#: data/nation/tupi.ruleset:5
msgid "Tupi"
msgstr "tupisch"

#: data/nation/tupi.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Tupi"
msgstr "Tupi"

#: data/nation/tupi.ruleset:9
msgid ""
"The Tupi are a native Brazilian people related to the Guarani who inhabited "
"the modern Brazilian states of Paraiba, Pernambuco, Ceara, Rio Grande do "
"Norte, Alagoas, Sergipe and others as well. Their chiefdoms were destroyed "
"through Portuguese slave-raids, the creation of mission-villages, and "
"disease. The Tupi intermarried with African slaves and Europeans alike and a "
"great many Brazilian place names are derived from Tupi words. "
msgstr ""
"Die Tupi sind Ureinwohner Brasiliens und mit den Guarani, die die heutigen "
"brasilianischen Staaten Paraiba, Pernambuco, Ceara, Rio Grande do Norte, "
"Alagoas, Sergipe und einige weitere bewohnten, verwandt. Ihre Stämme wurden "
"im Zuge zahlreicher portugiesischer Raubüberfälle versklavt, missioniert, "
"oder starben an Krankheiten. Sie vermischten sich sowohl mit afrikanischen "
"Sklaven als auch mit Europäern, sodass viele heute bekannte brasilianische "
"Ortsnamen aus tupischen Wörtern entstanden sind."

#: data/nation/turk.ruleset:5
msgid "Turkish"
msgstr "türkisch"

#: data/nation/turk.ruleset:6
msgid "?plural:Turks"
msgstr "Türken"

#: data/nation/turk.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"Modern Turkey is the successor state of the Ottoman Empire, which collapsed "
"and was dismembered by the victors in World War I after backing the Central "
"Powers. The country was subsequently reformed and secularized by Kemal "
"Mustapha, the hero of the defense of Gallipoli."
msgstr ""
"Die heutige Türkei ist der Nachfolgestaat des Ottomanischen Reiches, das im "
"ersten Weltkrieg die Zentralmächte unterstützte und von den Siegern geteilt "
"wurde. Im Anschluss wurde das Land von Kemal Mustafa, dem Helden der "
"Verteidigung von Gallipoli, reformiert und säkularisiert."

#: data/nation/turk.ruleset:30
#, c-format
msgid "%s Pasha"
msgstr "%s-Pascha"

#: data/nation/turk.ruleset:30
#, c-format
msgid "?female:%s Pasha"
msgstr "%s-Pascha"

#: data/nation/viking.ruleset:8
msgid ""
"The Vikings raided and traded along the coasts of Europe between 800 CE and "
"1100 CE. Viking raiders eventually became the rulers of Normandy, Russia, "
"and a short-lived kingdom in Sicily."
msgstr ""
"Die Wikinger raubten und handelten an Europas Küsten zwischen 800 und 1100. "
"Wikingische Räuber wurden schließlich die Herrscher der Normandie, von "
"Russland, und, für kurze Zeit, des Königreiches Sizilien."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:87
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A city with Airport can airlift one unit per turn (including aircraft). "
"Airlifting instantly transports the unit from one city to another and will "
"use all of the unit's movement points. A unit must have some movement points "
"left to be airlifted, and cannot carry cargo. The current setting (unlimited "
"to destination) means that the destination city does not need to have an "
"airport."
msgstr ""
"Eine Einheit mit Bewegungspunkten kann in einem Zug von einer Stadt mit "
"Flughafen zu einer anderen Stadt mit Flughafen transportiert werden. Dabei "
"werden alle Bewegungspunkte der Einheit verbraucht. Von einem Flughafen kann "
"nur ein Transport pro Runde durchgeführt werden."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:219
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the luxury good and tax output in a city by an additional 30%. "
"With both a Bank and a Marketplace in a city, the total bonus is 80%."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht die Luxusproduktion und Steuereinnahmen der Stadt um 50%. Zusammen "
"mit einer Bank und einem Marktplatz erhält die Stadt einen Gesamtbonus von "
"100%."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:225
#, fuzzy
msgid "Mercantile Exchange"
msgstr "Mehrspieler-Regelsatz"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:243
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the luxury good and tax output in a city by an additional 30%. "
"With a Mercantile Exchange, a Bank and a Marketplace in a city, the total "
"bonus is 110%."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht die Luxusproduktion und Steuereinnahmen der Stadt um 50%. Zusammen "
"mit einer Bank und einem Marktplatz erhält die Stadt einen Gesamtbonus von "
"100%."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:269
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks, each new land unit built in a city (except siege units like "
"Catapults) will automatically have Veteran status, which means that its "
"attack and defense strengths are increased by 50%."
msgstr ""
"Mit Kasernen ist eine Stadt in der Lage, Landeinheiten mit Veteranenstatus "
"herzustellen, d.h. Einheiten, deren Angriffs- und Verteidigungswerte um 50% "
"erhöht sind. Außerdem werden Landeinheiten, die bewegungslos eine ganze "
"Runde in der Stadt verweilen, vollständig kuriert."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:298
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks II, each new land unit built in a city (except siege units "
"like Cannon and Artillery) will automatically have Veteran status, which "
"means that its attack and defense strengths are increased by 50%."
msgstr ""
"Mit Kasernen ist eine Stadt in der Lage, Landeinheiten mit Veteranenstatus "
"herzustellen, d.h. Einheiten, deren Angriffs- und Verteidigungswerte um 50% "
"erhöht sind. Außerdem werden Landeinheiten, die bewegungslos eine ganze "
"Runde in der Stadt verweilen, vollständig kuriert."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:326
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With a Barracks III, each new land unit built in a city (except siege units "
"like Artillery and Howitzer) will automatically have Veteran status, which "
"means that its attack and defense strengths are increased by 50%."
msgstr ""
"Mit Kasernen ist eine Stadt in der Lage, Landeinheiten mit Veteranenstatus "
"herzustellen, d.h. Einheiten, deren Angriffs- und Verteidigungswerte um 50% "
"erhöht sind. Außerdem werden Landeinheiten, die bewegungslos eine ganze "
"Runde in der Stadt verweilen, vollständig kuriert."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:354 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:319
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Cathedral makes 3 unhappy citizens content in a city, making it easier to "
"maintain order in that city. However, it does not affect citizens made "
"unhappy by aggression. Knowledge of Theology increases the effect of a "
"Cathedral, making an additional unhappy citizen content, except under "
"Communism."
msgstr ""
"Eine Kathedrale stellt drei Unzufriedene einer Stadt zufrieden und "
"erleichtert es somit, die Ordnung aufrecht zu erhalten; wegen militärischer "
"Aktivitäten unzufriedene Bürger betrifft dies jedoch nicht. Nach Entdeckung "
"der Theologie stellt sie einen zusätzlichen Unzufriedenen zufrieden; nach "
"Entdeckung des Kommunismus stellt sie einen Unzufriedenen weniger zufrieden."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:381 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"City Walls make it easier to defend a city. They add a +100% bonus to the "
"intrinsic defense strength of units within the city against land units (that "
"is a two-thirds increase for small cities, or a one-half increase for cities "
"larger than size 8), but are ineffective against airborne and sea units. "
"City Walls also prevent the loss of population which occurs when a defending "
"unit is defeated by a land unit."
msgstr ""
"Eine Stadtmauer hilft, eine Stadt zu schützen, indem sie einen 100%igen "
"Bonus auf die ursprüngliche Verteidigungskraft in der Stadt stationierter "
"Einheiten gegenüber angreifenden Landeinheiten gewährt (das ist eine um zwei "
"Drittel für kleine Städte bzw. um die Hälfte für Städte größer 8 erhöhte "
"Verteidigungskraft). Gegenüber Luft- und Seeeinheiten ist sie jedoch "
"wirkungslos. Auch verhindert sie Verluste bei der Bevölkerung, falls "
"gegnerische Landeinheiten eine in der Stadt stationierte Einheit vernichten."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:487
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the shield production in a city by 50%, or 100% with an electrical "
"plant of any kind in the same city."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht die Schildproduktion in einer Stadt um 25%, zusammen mit einem "
"Elektrizitätswerk welcher Art auch immer sogar um 50%."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:513
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"When any small city grows or shrinks, 50 % of food points are saved. This "
"helps cities to grow faster and more easily withstand famine. With a Granary "
"this is extended to cities of size 4 and above. "
msgstr ""
"Wann immer eine kleine Stadt wächst oder schrumpft, werden 10 Nahrungspunkte "
"gesichert, wodurch den Städten ein schnelleres Wachstum ermöglicht und das "
"Risiko einer Hungersnot verringert wird. Zusammen mit einem Kornspeicher "
"können Städte über eine Größe von 4 hinaus wachsen. (Kleine Städte benötigen "
"zehn Nahrungspunkte für einen Wachstumsschritt, spätere Schritte benötigen "
"mehr.)"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:546
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Gives one extra food resource on all Ocean or Deep Ocean tiles (but not "
"Lakes). The city needs to be coastal (next to one of these tiles) to build "
"this improvement."
msgstr ""
"Gibt +1 Nahrung von allen Ozean- und Tiefseefeldern, nicht aber von Seen. "
"Kann nur von Küstenstädten gebaut werden."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:572 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:716
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:908 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1127
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any kind of electrical plant increases the shield production effects of a "
"Factory or Mfg. Plant in its city by 50% each. Thus, an electrical plant in "
"combination with either a Factory or Mfg. Plant gives a 100% production "
"bonus over the level without any of these improvements. An electrical plant, "
"Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a 200% production bonus. The extra "
"production may lead to the city generating more pollution."
msgstr ""
"Elektrizitätswerke jeglicher Art steigern die Produktion von Fabriken und "
"Fertigungsstätten um jeweils 25%, d.h. bei Existenz eines dieser Bauwerke "
"wird die Produktion um 50% im Vergleich zur Situation ohne jegliche Gebäude "
"erhöht. Sind beide vorhanden, erhöht sich der Bonus auf 100%, allerdings "
"vergrößert sich durch die zusätzliche Produktion die durch die Stadt "
"verursachte Umweltverschmutzung."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:655
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Reduces the pollution generated by the population in a city. This building "
"counteracts the additional pollution associated with any two other "
"buildings. It also increases the working area for the city."
msgstr ""
"Reduziert die durch die Bevölkerung verursachte Umweltverschmutzung. Diese "
"Einrichtung hebt die Auswirkungen zweier die Verschmutzung erhöhender "
"Stadtverbesserungen auf."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:680
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the shield production in a city by an additional 50%, or 100% with "
"an electrical plant of any kind in the same city. This effect is cumulative "
"with that of a Factory."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht die Schildproduktion in einer Stadt um weitere 25%, zusammen mit "
"einem Elektrizitätswerk welche Art auch immer sogar um 50%. Der Effekt "
"addiert sich mit demjenigen einer Fabrik."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:684 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:641
msgid ""
"With sufficient shield production, cities with a Manufacturing Plant can "
"produce up to two units each turn (but only single units of types which cost "
"population)."
msgstr ""
"Bei ausreichender Produktion kann eine Stadt mit einer Fabrik bis zu zwei "
"Einheiten pro Runde erzeugen (aber nur einzelne Einheiten von Typen, die "
"Bevölkerung kosten)."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:725 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:681
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"However, a Nuclear Plant also reduces the pollution associated with shield "
"production to 50% of its normal value, or 25% in combination with a "
"Recycling Center. (Its effect is the same as that of a Hydro Plant.)"
msgstr ""
"Ein Kernkraftwerk reduziert die mit der Produktion zusammenhängende "
"Umweltverschmutzung um die hälfte ihres normalen Werts, oder um ein Viertel, "
"wenn ein Recycling-Zentrum vorhanden ist. (Der Effekt ist der gleiche wie "
"bei einem Wasserkraftwerk.)"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:755 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:711
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Every Ocean or Lake tile worked by the city yields one extra shield "
"resource, as well as any Deep Ocean tile containing an oil platform. The "
"city needs to be next to a water tile to build this improvement."
msgstr ""
"+1 Schild von allen Ozeanfeldern und von Tiefseefeldern mit Bojen. Kann nur "
"von Küstenstädten gebaut werden."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:778 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:734
msgid ""
"Makes a city the capital and the center of your government. Waste in other "
"cities (corruption, production waste, and food waste) is often related to "
"how far away from the capital they are. On top of this, corruption and "
"production waste in your capital itself is half of what it would otherwise "
"be (and a Courthouse will eliminate it entirely)."
msgstr ""
"Macht eine Stadt zur Hauptstadt und somit zum Regierungssitz. Oftmals ist "
"die Korruption in anderen Städten davon abhängig, wie weit diese von der "
"Hauptstadt entfernt sind; darüber hinaus sind Korruption und Verschwendung "
"in der Hauptstadt selbst nur halb so schlimm wie üblich, ein Gerichtsgebäude "
"beseitigt sie vollständig."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:806
#, fuzzy
msgid "2nd Palace"
msgstr "Palast"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:822
msgid ""
"Makes a city the 2nd capital, that acts as a second center of government."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:825 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:781
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Waste in other cities (corruption, production waste, and food waste) is "
"related to how far away from the nearest capital they are. On top of this, "
"corruption and production waste in the capital itself is half of what it "
"would otherwise be (and a Courthouse will eliminate it entirely)."
msgstr ""
"Macht eine Stadt zur Hauptstadt und somit zum Regierungssitz. Oftmals ist "
"die Korruption in anderen Städten davon abhängig, wie weit diese von der "
"Hauptstadt entfernt sind; darüber hinaus sind Korruption und Verschwendung "
"in der Hauptstadt selbst nur halb so schlimm wie üblich, ein Gerichtsgebäude "
"beseitigt sie vollständig."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:831
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The city where this second palace is located cannot be incited to revolt, "
"and enjoys a bonus when enemy agents try to evade your own agents stationed "
"in the city, or sabotage your buildings."
msgstr ""
"In allen Regierungsformen hängen auch die Kosten, die ein feindlicher "
"Diplomat oder Spion zur Anstiftung zu einer Revolte in einer Stadt benötigt, "
"von der Entfernung zur Hauptstadt ab. In der Hauptstadt selbst kann zur "
"Revolte nicht angestiftet werden, zudem genießt sie einen Bonus im Bezug auf "
"feindliche Agenten, die Ihre in der Stadt stationierten Agenten umgehen oder "
"Gebäude in der Stadt sabotieren wollen."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:940 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:894
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Building a Recycling Center reduces the amount of pollution generated by "
"shield production in a city by 50%, or by an additional 25% in cities with "
"another building which reduces pollution (Nuclear Plant, Hydro Plant, or "
"Solar Plant)."
msgstr ""
"Ein Recycling-Zentrum vermindert die durch Produktion verursachte "
"Umweltverschmutzung einer Stadt um die Hälfte. Ist ein weiteres die "
"Umweltverschmutzung reduzierendes Bauwerk vorhanden (Kern-, Wasser- oder "
"Solarkraftwerk), vermindert sie sich um ein weiteres Viertel."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:969 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:922
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"The total bonus is 150% if a Library, a University, and a Research Lab are "
"all present in the same city, increasing to 300% once the Great Library, "
"Isaac Newton's College, and the Internet have all been built."
msgstr ""
"Der Gesamtbonus beträgt 150% wenn eine Bibliothek, eine Universität und ein "
"Forschungslabor alle in derselben Stadt vorhanden sind, was sich auf sogar "
"300% erhöht, wenn die Große Bibliothek, Isaac Newtons Universität und das "
"Internet gebaut bzw. entwickelt worden sind."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:993 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:946
msgid ""
"Doubles the intrinsic defense strength of units within a city when defending "
"against aircraft (including helicopters)."
msgstr ""
"Verdoppelt die ursprüngliche Verteidigungsstärke aller in der Stadt "
"stationierten Einheiten gegenüber allen Luftwaffeneinheiten einschließlich "
"Helikoptern."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:999
#, fuzzy
msgid "SDI Defense I"
msgstr "SDI-Verteidigung"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1015
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Protects a city and its environs (up to 2 tiles away) from attacks by other "
"nations' Nuclear units. A Nuclear unit not owned by you or a teammate which "
"attacks a city with SDI Defense, or attacks a unit (or is deliberately "
"exploded) within range, may be shot down and simply has no effect. Also, "
"adds 30% to the intrinsic defense strength of units in the city when "
"defending against conventional missiles. SDI I + capital protects against "
"100% of the nuclear attacks while SDI I only defends against 30% of the "
"attacks. SDI I + Palace adds 100% to the defense against missiles. NOTE: The "
"Palace City gets 100% SDI defense with the Palace and with SDI I. SDI II and "
"SDI III are not needed."
msgstr ""
"Schützt eine Stadt und ihre Umgebung (bis zu zwei Felder weit) vor Angriffen "
"durch Nuklearwaffen. Wenn eine nukleare Einheit, die weder Ihnen noch einem "
"Ihrer Verbündeten gehört, eine Stadt mit einer SDI-Anlage oder eine Einheit "
"in der Reichweite der Anlage angreift (oder absichtlich gesprengt wird), "
"wird sie abgeschossen und hat schlicht keinen Effekt. Verdoppelt zudem die "
"ursprünglichen Verteidigungswerte von Einheiten in der Stadt gegenüber "
"nichtnuklearen Raketen."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1027
#, fuzzy
msgid "SDI Defense II"
msgstr "SDI-Verteidigung"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1044
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Protects a city and its environs (up to 2 tiles away) from attacks by other "
"nations' Nuclear units. A Nuclear unit not owned by you or a teammate which "
"attacks a city with SDI Defense, or attacks a unit (or is deliberately "
"exploded) within range, may be shot down and simply has no effect. Also, "
"adds 30% to the intrinsic defense strength of units in the city when "
"defending against conventional missiles. SDI II adds another 30% against the "
"nuclear attacks. NOTE: The Palace City gets 100% SDI defense with the Palace "
"and with SDI I. SDI II and SDI III are not needed. The Palace with SDI II "
"but without SDI I doesn't give 100% defense against nukes."
msgstr ""
"Schützt eine Stadt und ihre Umgebung (bis zu zwei Felder weit) vor Angriffen "
"durch Nuklearwaffen. Wenn eine nukleare Einheit, die weder Ihnen noch einem "
"Ihrer Verbündeten gehört, eine Stadt mit einer SDI-Anlage oder eine Einheit "
"in der Reichweite der Anlage angreift (oder absichtlich gesprengt wird), "
"wird sie abgeschossen und hat schlicht keinen Effekt. Verdoppelt zudem die "
"ursprünglichen Verteidigungswerte von Einheiten in der Stadt gegenüber "
"nichtnuklearen Raketen."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1056
#, fuzzy
msgid "SDI Defense III"
msgstr "SDI-Verteidigung"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1073
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Protects a city and its environs (up to 2 tiles away) from attacks by other "
"nations' Nuclear units. A Nuclear unit not owned by you or a teammate which "
"attacks a city with SDI Defense, or attacks a unit (or is deliberately "
"exploded) within range, may be shot down and simply has no effect. Also, "
"adds 40% to the intrinsic defense strength of units in the city when "
"defending against conventional missiles. SDI III adds another 30% against "
"the nuclear attacks. NOTE: The Palace City gets 100% SDI defense with the "
"Palace and with SDI I. SDI II and SDI III are not needed. The Palace with "
"SDI III but without SDI I doesn't give 100% defense against nukes."
msgstr ""
"Schützt eine Stadt und ihre Umgebung (bis zu zwei Felder weit) vor Angriffen "
"durch Nuklearwaffen. Wenn eine nukleare Einheit, die weder Ihnen noch einem "
"Ihrer Verbündeten gehört, eine Stadt mit einer SDI-Anlage oder eine Einheit "
"in der Reichweite der Anlage angreift (oder absichtlich gesprengt wird), "
"wird sie abgeschossen und hat schlicht keinen Effekt. Verdoppelt zudem die "
"ursprünglichen Verteidigungswerte von Einheiten in der Stadt gegenüber "
"nichtnuklearen Raketen."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1170 data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1210
#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1241
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Before you can build any spaceship parts, the Apollo Program wonder must "
"have been built by any player. The city must also have a Factory, Library, "
"University, and a Research Lab."
msgstr ""
"Bevor Sie Raumschiffkomponenten bauen können, muss das Apollo-Programm von "
"irgendeinem Spieler fertig gestellt worden sein."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1266
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the luxury good and tax output in a city by an additional 40%, or "
"65% if Super Highways are also in the city. A Marketplace, Bank, Mercantile "
"Exchange, and Stock Exchange together in a city yield a total bonus of 150%. "
"Adding Super Highways yields a total of 175%."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht das Luxus- und Steueraufkommen in einer Stadt um 50% bzw. um 100% "
"wenn Autobahnen vorhanden sind. Ein Marktplatz, eine Bank und eine Börse "
"führen in einer Stadt zu einem Gesamtbonus von 150%, kommen Autobahnen dazu, "
"sogar 200%."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1290 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1177
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Each tile around the city with roads and without farmland, that is already "
"generating some trade, produces one extra trade resource. The same applies "
"to the city center tile (even if it is receiving a farmland bonus)."
msgstr ""
"Jedes Straßenfeld der Stadt, auf dem sich kein Ackerland befindet und "
"welches bereits Handelspunkte erwirtschaftet, erzeugt einen extra "
"Handelspunkt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1295 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1182
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Also doubles the effect of any Stock Exchange in the city (increasing luxury "
"good and tax output by an additional 50%)."
msgstr ""
"Verdoppelt die Auswirkungen einer Börse in der Stadt (erhöht das Luxus- und "
"Steueraufkommen um weitere 50%)."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1344 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1230
msgid ""
"Makes one unhappy citizen content. The Mysticism advance doubles this effect "
"(except under a Communist government). With both Mysticism and the Temple of "
"Artemis, 4 citizens are made content (3 under Communism). Does not affect "
"citizens made unhappy by aggression."
msgstr ""
"Stellt einen unzufriedenen Bürger zufrieden. Sowohl die Erkenntnisse über "
"die Mystik als auch der Artemistempel verdoppeln den Effekt (außer in "
"kommunistischen Ländern). Somit können bis zu vier Unzufriedene zufrieden "
"gestellt werden (drei im Kommunismus). Hat keine Auswirkungen auf Bürger, "
"die wegen militärischer Aktivitäten unzufrieden sind."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1427 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1312
msgid ""
"In every city with a Stock Exchange, city improvements which would normally "
"have an upkeep of 1 become free of upkeep. (Communist governments inherently "
"give this benefit, so there is no bonus under Communism.)"
msgstr ""
"Städte mit einer Börse müssen keinen Unterhalt für Gebäude bezahlen, die "
"normalerweise 1 Gold unterhalt erfordern würden. Da kommunistische "
"Regierungen diesen Unterhalt generell nicht zahlen müssen, erhalten sie in "
"dieser Hinsicht keinen zusätzlichen Bonus."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1501
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This stunning technological achievement makes one content citizen happy in "
"each of your cities (2 extra luxury per city). It further reduces your risk "
"of plague (by 10% of the base chance). With knowledge of Medicine, any of "
"your cities with an Aqueduct and a Sewer System will be entirely free of "
"plague."
msgstr ""
"Diese faszinierende technologische Errungenschaft macht in jeder Ihre Städte "
"einen Zufriedenen glücklich (2 extra Luxuspunkte). Außerdem reduziert es die "
"Gefahr einer Krankheit in Ihren Städten um 10% der Grundwahrscheinlichkeit, "
"zusammen mit einem Aquädukt, einem Abwassersystem und dem Wissen um die "
"Medizin wird das Seuchenrisiko vollständig gebannt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1526 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1410
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Charles Darwin's Voyage sparked the discovery of the evolution of the "
"species, which inspired greater confidence in science. All your cities "
"generate 1 extra science bulb."
msgstr ""
"Die Forschungsreise des Charles Darwin war der Anfangspunkt der modernen "
"Evolutionstheorie der Arten, die ein größeres Vertrauen in die Wissenschaft "
"zur Folge hatte. Alle Ihre Städte erzeugen einen extra Forschungspunkt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1577
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Gives an immediate technology advance to the player that builds it, and "
"thereafter 10 extra research points every turn to its city."
msgstr ""
"Führt bei dem errichtenden Spieler zu der sofortigen Entdeckung einer "
"weiteren Technologie und zu vier weiteren Forschungspunkten pro Runde in "
"seiner Stadt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1580
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Completion of this wonder permanently adds 50% to the effect of Libraries "
"for every player."
msgstr ""
"Die Fertigstellung dieses Weltwunders verdoppelt die Auswirkungen von "
"Bibliotheken für alle Spieler dauerhaft."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1604
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Increases the defense of all your cities by adding a +40% bonus to its "
"units' intrinsic defense strength against land units (this is cumulative "
"with any City Walls), and preventing the loss of population which occurs "
"when a defending unit is defeated by a land unit."
msgstr ""
"Erhöht die Verteidigungsstärke Ihrer Städte gegen Landeinheiten um 50% auf "
"den ursprünglichen Wert der stationierten Einheiten. Der Effekt addiert sich "
"mit demjenigen der Stadtmauern, außerdem wird der Bevölkerungsverlust "
"verhindert, der ansonsten bei Überwindung einer Verteidigereinheit durch "
"eine Landeinheit einträte."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1629 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1512
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Makes one unhappy citizen content in every city of the player that owns it "
"(not including citizens unhappy about aggression). This wonder also makes "
"two content citizens happy in the city where it is located (4 extra luxury "
"good points)."
msgstr ""
"Stellt in jeder Stadt des Eigentümers einen Bürger zufrieden, der nicht "
"wegen militärischer Aktivitäten unzufrieden ist. Darüber hinaus werden in "
"der Stadt, in der dieses Weltwunder steht, zwei zufriedene Bürger glücklich "
"(4 extra Luxuspunkte)."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1680
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Gives an immediate technology advance to the player that builds it, and "
"thereafter 12 extra research points every turn to its city."
msgstr ""
"Führt bei dem errichtenden Spieler zu der sofortigen Entdeckung einer "
"weiteren Technologie und zu vier weiteren Forschungspunkten pro Runde in "
"seiner Stadt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1683
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Completion of this wonder permanently adds 50% to the effect of Universities "
"for every player."
msgstr ""
"Die Fertigstellung dieses Weltwunders verdoppelt dauerhaft die Auswirkungen "
"von Universitäten für alle Spieler."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1705 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1587
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Makes one content citizen happy in every city of the player that owns it (2 "
"extra luxury good points per city)."
msgstr ""
"In jeder Stadt des Eigentümers werden zwei zufriedene Bürger glücklich (2 "
"extra Luxuspunkte pro Stadt)."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1728 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1610
msgid ""
"Reduces the unhappiness caused by aggressively deployed military units owned "
"by the city by 1 -- in other words, it neutralizes the unhappiness caused by "
"a single military unit (except under Democracy, where a single unit makes "
"two citizens unhappy). Under governments where unit upkeep is paid in gold, "
"it gives two free gold per city towards upkeep every turn."
msgstr ""
"Verringert die Anzahl der wegen aggressiver militärischer Aktionen "
"Unzufriedenen um eins — im Klartext: neutralisiert die durch eine einzelne "
"Militäreinheit erzeugte Unzufriedenheit (außer in der Demokratie, in der "
"eine einzelne Einheit zwei unzufriedene Bürger nach sich zieht). In "
"Regierungsformen, in welchen Unterhalt in Gold gezahlt wird, werden umsonst "
"zwei Gold zusätzlich zum Unterhalt beigesteuert."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1755
#, fuzzy
msgid "Upgrades two obsolete units per game turn for free."
msgstr "Modernisiert zwei veraltete Einheiten pro Spielrunde."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1760
#, fuzzy
msgid "Verrocchio's Workshop"
msgstr "Leonardos Werkstatt"

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1777
msgid ""
"Upgrades one obsolete unit per game turn for free. The workshop where "
"Leonardo da Vinci was a garzone (studio boy) before he was able to set up "
"his own workshop."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1801 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1660
msgid ""
"Gives all your sea units 1 additional movement point (except Triremes while "
"moving on rivers). Makes all your new sea units veterans (for all your "
"cities)."
msgstr ""
"Alle Marineeinheiten außer Triremen auf Flüssen erhalten einen zusätzlichen "
"Bewegungspunkt. In allen eigenen Städten erhalten neue Marineeinheiten den "
"Veteranengrad."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1850
msgid ""
"The Manhattan Project will make it possible to build nuclear weapons. After "
"it is built, anyone with the necessary technological advances can build "
"nuclear weapons. The Nuclear Fission advance is required to build the early "
"Nuclear Bomb, which is unique to a nation: each nation can have only one at "
"a time. The Robotics advance is required to build the later Nuclear units, "
"which are not limited in number."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1875
#, c-format
msgid ""
"Increases trade output by 30% in all cities for all the players. The player "
"owning this wonder is the only one able to build the Trade Company. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1878
msgid ""
"TIP: it may make sense to let someone else to build this wonder. Everyone "
"gets the effect and the Trade Conpany can't usually be instantly built after "
"Marco Polo is finished."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1884
msgid "Trade Company"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1901
#, c-format
msgid ""
"This wonder gives the player extra trade with far away countries. Increases "
"trade output by 10% in all cities owned by the player."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1908
msgid "Atlantic Telegraph Company"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1925
msgid ""
"The world will become smaller place with when the new means of communication "
"connect all the people over the globe. All the players will get an embassy "
"with all the players. The city where the wonder is located gets extra trade "
"for each tile already producing trade."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:1999 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1802
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Reduces by 1 the unhappiness caused by one aggressively deployed military "
"unit per city -- in other words, in each city it neutralizes the unhappiness "
"caused by a single military unit (except under Democracy, where it just "
"halves the unhappiness from that unit). Each city also avoids one shield of "
"upkeep for units."
msgstr ""
"Verringert die Anzahl der wegen aggressiv eingesetzter Militäreinheiten aus "
"dieser Stadt verursachte Unzufriedenheit um eins, d.h. neutralisiert die "
"durch eine einzelne Militäreinheit verursachte Unzufriedenheit (außer in der "
"Demokratie, in der eine einzelne Militäreinheit zwei Bürger unzufrieden "
"macht). Außerdem ist in jeder Stadt ein Schild weniger Unterhalt für "
"Einheiten erforderlich."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2049 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1852
msgid ""
"Each tile around the city where this wonder is built that is already "
"generating some shield output produces one extra shield resource. Under "
"Despotism or Tribal governments, the Pyramids cancel the penalty to worked "
"tiles with output greater than 2 (for all kinds of output), as if all your "
"cities were always celebrating."
msgstr ""
"Jedes Feld der Stadt, in der dieses Weltwunder steht, und das zumindest "
"einen Produktionspunkt erwirtschaftet, produziert einen zusätzlichen "
"Produktionspunkt. In diktatorischen Regimen und in Stammesverbänden heben "
"die Pyramiden die Beschränkung auf zwei Erzeugnisse pro Feld auf, so, als ob "
"alle Ihre Städte feierten."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2079
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Completion of this wonder permanently adds 50% to the effect of Research "
"Labs for every player."
msgstr ""
"Die Fertigstellung dieses Weltwunders verdoppelt den Effekt von "
"Forschungslabors für alle Spieler dauerhaft."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2102
msgid ""
"Gives 1 additional luxury to every city, and 6 luxuries to the city where it "
"is located."
msgstr ""
"+1 Luxus in jeder Stadt, und +6 Luxus in der Stadt, in der es sich befindet."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2128
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All your new military land units start with an additional veteran level This "
"is cumulative with any Barracks building in a city. With both, units are "
"created as veteran 2."
msgstr ""
"Neue Landeinheiten erhalten automatisch einen weiteren Veteranengrad, "
"zusätzlich zu den Auswirkungen einer Kaserne. Mit beidem werden Einheiten "
"also unmittelbar als Generäle ausgebildet."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2151 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1979
msgid ""
"Creates a world senate that prevents unprovoked declaration of war by any "
"nuclear-capable nation (that is, any nation with knowledge of Nuclear "
"Fission, once the Manhattan Project has been built). AI players are more "
"inclined to be friendly and forgiving toward the owner of this wonder. These "
"effects last until the Apollo Program is completed."
msgstr ""
"Errichtet einen Weltsenat, der die unprovozierte Kriegserklärung von nicht "
"nuklear aufgerüsteten Staaten verhindert, also solcher Staaten, die nach "
"Abschluss des Manhattan-Projekts noch keine Kenntnisse über die Kernspaltung "
"erworben haben. KI-Spieler verhalten sich freundlicher und nachsichtiger "
"gegenüber dem Eigentümer dieses Weltwunders, was sich allerdings mit "
"Abschluss des Apollo-Programms ändert."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2158 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1986
msgid ""
"Also, if any player's city is in disorder for more than two turns in a row, "
"that player's government falls (even for governments other than Republic and "
"Democracy)."
msgstr ""
"Wenn sich irgendeine Stadt eines Spielers für mehr als zwei "
"aufeinanderfolgende Runden in Aufruhr befindet, wird die Regierung des "
"betreffenden Spielers gestürzt und sein Staat verfällt in Anarchie. Dies "
"gilt auch dann, wenn es sich um eine andere Regierungsform als Republik und "
"Demokratie handelt."

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2165
msgid "Hal Saflieni Hypogeum"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2182
msgid ""
"Ħal Saflieni Hypogeum is thought to have been a sanctuary and necropolis. It "
"pre-dates the Bronze Age and was one of the first, if not the first, shrines "
"built. With this wonder, the city having it will get +6 additional luxury "
"good points. The effect of this very early wonder ends with the invention of "
"bronze working. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/buildings.ruleset:2228
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Allows you to choose any government, including those that have not yet been "
"researched by your civilization. It also allows unprovoked declaration of "
"war regardless of any senate instituted by a Democracy or Federation "
"government or by the United Nations."
msgstr ""
"Gestattet die Wahl jeder Regierungsform (auch ohne entsprechende Kenntnisse) "
"ohne die Periode der Anarchie. Ferner erlaubt es die unprovozierte "
"Kriegserklärung an jeder demokratischen oder föderalen Kontrollinstanz "
"vorbei, sogar am Senat der Vereinten Nationen."

#: data/royale/cities.ruleset:58 data/sandbox/cities.ruleset:58
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Each entertainer produces two luxury good points for their city per turn, "
"increasing to three once any player has built Shakespeare's Theater. See the "
"section on Happiness for the effects of luxury good points."
msgstr ""
"Jeder Unterhalter produziert pro Runde zwei Luxuspunkte für seine Stadt, "
"drei, wenn der Spieler Shakespears Theater erbaut hat. Siehe den Abschnitt "
"über Zufriedenheit für den Effekt von Luxuspunkten."

#: data/royale/cities.ruleset:73 data/sandbox/cities.ruleset:73
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Each scientist adds two bulbs to your empire's research output per turn, "
"increasing to three once any player has built Darwin's Voyage."
msgstr ""
"Jeder Wissenschaftler führt pro Runde Ihrem Staat zwei Forschungspunkte zu, "
"ab der Vollendung von Darwins Reise durch irgendeinen Spieler drei."

#: data/royale/game.ruleset:26
#, fuzzy
msgid "Royale ruleset"
msgstr "Standardregelsatz"

#. TRANS: In the client, this is displayed alongside the contents of
#. ;    README.royale, which are not localized.
#: data/royale/game.ruleset:40
msgid ""
"You are playing Freeciv21 with Royale ruleset based on Longturn Traditional "
"LTT rules (originally based on civ2civ3):\n"
"\n"
"Gameplay more similar to classic 4x empire building games, keeping it easy "
"to learn but challenging to master.\n"
"\n"
"Also suitable for single player, with AI less aggressive at start, but more "
"challenging at the end.\n"
"\n"
"The Royale ruleset is designed to be played without AI players and allows "
"very fast gameplay meaning that one game does not take too much time. For "
"similar gameplay with more turns look for the LTT ruleset. and it is "
"balanced to make the game interesting for both beginners and experienced "
"players. Everything comes with a cost. Even advancing more than your "
"opponent. This keeps it challenging and fair to everyone."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:77
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Buildings and technologies do not require any upkeep.\n"
"* Each worked tile that gives more than 2 Food, Shield, or Trade will suffer "
"a -1 penalty, unless the city working it is celebrating. (Cities below size "
"3 will not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 1 "
"shield per turn.\n"
"* Military units do not cause unhappiness even when deployed aggressively.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 3 military units inside a city "
"will each force 1 unhappy citizen to become content.\n"
"* You have no control over national budget. Half of the trade income is "
"simply lost to your economy (less if you have luxury-promoting buildings), "
"and the remainder all goes to luxuries. Conventional corruption increases "
"with distance from the capital (half as fast with knowledge of The "
"Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 30%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks.\n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or more."
msgstr ""
"• Stadtverbesserungen und Technologien erfordern keinen Unterhalt.\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu zwei Einheiten ohne Kosten unterstützen; jede "
"weitere Einheit verursacht 1 Schild Kosten pro Runde.\n"
"• Militäreinheiten verursachen auch dann keine Unzufriedenheit, wenn sie "
"aggressiv eingsetzt werden.\n"
"• Sie haben keine Kontrolle über die Steuersätze. Die Hälfte des "
"Handelseinkommens geht schlicht an die Wirtschaft verloren, der Rest wird in "
"Luxus umgewandelt. Die konventionelle Korruption erhöht sich mit der "
"Entfernung von der Hauptstadt (ab der Entdeckung der Firma nur noch halb so "
"schnell).\n"
"• Der Grundverlust in der Produktion beträgt 30%. Dies erhöht sich mit "
"zunehmender Entfernung von der Hauptstadt (ab der Entdeckung des Handels nur "
"noch halb so schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:96
msgid ""
"Playing with Anarchy? \n"
"You do not usually want to play with Anarchy but you need to when there is a "
"need to switch the government. For these situations you may want to plan "
"your production so that you have some gold reserve before switching to "
"Anarchy and also not using that many trade tiles while in Anarchy. You may "
"also want to explore the options to make your cities to celebrate while in "
"Anarchy. This way you may be able to make your cities to celebrate when you "
"switch to your new government. If you have only some bulbs left from getting "
"the governent you want it may make sense to revolt early and complete the "
"research with scientists. This may be very useful especially when you switch "
"away from Tribalism or Despotism because you may get the desired government "
"a turn or two early."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:123
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Compared to Despotism, a Tribal economy is more shield-oriented. Its bonuses "
"to veterancy can be an advantage in wartime."
msgstr ""
"Im Vergleich zur Diktatur ist eine stammesrechtlich geführte Wirtschaft "
"produktiver. Ihre Boni in der Veteranenschaft und ein starkes Kriegsrecht "
"können in Zeiten militärischer Konfrontation von Vorteil sein."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:126
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Increases by half the chance of land units getting the next veteran level "
"after a battle.\n"
"* Each worked tile that gives more than 2 Food, Shield, or Trade will suffer "
"a -1 penalty, unless the city working it is celebrating. (Cities below size "
"3 will not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 1 "
"shield per turn.\n"
"* Unlike later governments, military units do not cause unhappiness even "
"when deployed aggressively.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 3 military units inside a city "
"will each force 1 unhappy citizen to become content.\n"
"* Base corruption is 30% (the highest under any government). This increases "
"with distance from the capital (half as fast with knowledge of The "
"Corporation).\n"
"* There is no base level of production waste, but an increasing amount with "
"distance from the capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or more."
msgstr ""
"• Erhöht die Wahrscheinlichkeit, dass Landeinheiten nach einem Kampf den "
"nächsten Veteranengrad erreichen, um die Hälfte.\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann umsonst bis zu zwei Einheiten unterstützen; jede weitere "
"Einheit kostet ein Schild pro Runde.\n"
"• Anders als in späteren Regierungsformen führen militärische Einheiten auch "
"dann nicht zu Unzufriedenheit, wenn sie aggressiv eingesetzt werden.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 30% (die höchste unter allen "
"Regierungsformen). Sie erhöht sich mit der Entfernung von der Hauptstadt (ab "
"Entdeckung der Firma nur noch halb so schnell).\n"
"• Es gibt keine Grundverschwendung in der Produktion, aber sie erhöht sich "
"dennoch mit einer größeren Entfernung zur Hauptstadt (ab Entdeckung des "
"Handels nur noch halb so schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:145
msgid ""
"Playing with Tribal? \n"
"Tribal nations get more production and are able to maintain more units for "
"free. Tribal is a very good alternative for someone who is not planning to "
"go Monarchy first. Instead you may want to consider building Ħal Saflieni "
"Hypogeum in your capital city and also building the Pyramids as fast as "
"possible to that you will get rid of the -1 tile penalty related to Anarchy, "
"Despotism, and Tribalism. It will also make sense to revolt during the first "
"turn. This way you may lose less production because of Anarchy. If you play "
"well you will get the Pyramids around T15 - T20 and this will keep your "
"empire competive even until the mid game. The catch however is that you may "
"be too comfortable with the Tribalism and switch to another government too "
"late. This is why you may want to consider switching around T40 - T60. In "
"short Tribalism helps fast expansion more compared to Despotism."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:176
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Your centers of government (cities with Palace and 2nd Palace) get a +75% "
"bonus to gold production.\n"
"* Each worked tile that gives more than 2 Food, Shield, or Trade will suffer "
"a -1 penalty, unless the city working it is celebrating. (Cities below size "
"3 will not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 1 "
"gold per turn.\n"
"* Unlike later governments, military units do not cause unhappiness even "
"when deployed aggressively.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 20 military units inside a city "
"will each force 1 unhappy citizen to become content.\n"
"* Base corruption is 20%. This increases with distance from the capital "
"(half as fast with knowledge of The Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 10%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or more."
msgstr ""
"• Ihre Hauptstadt erhält einen Bonus von 50% auf ihre Goldproduktion.\n"
"• Feiernde Städte erzeugen einen extra Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, welches "
"bereits Handel erzeugt (Städte kleiner 3 werden nicht feiern).\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu drei Einheiten umsonst unterstützen; jede weitere "
"Einheit kostet ein Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert bis zu 3 aggressiv eingesetzte Militäreinheiten, jede "
"weitere verursacht einen unzufriedenen Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 10% und erhöht sich mit der Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt (ab Entdeckung der Firma nur noch halb so schnell).\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 20% und wächst mit "
"zunehmender Entfernung von der Hauptstadt (ab Entdeckung des Handels nur "
"noch halb so schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:194
msgid ""
"Playing with Despotism? \n"
"With Despotism you get slightly better science and if you plan to go for "
"Monarchy this may be your choice. Despotism is a very good alternative for "
"someone who is planning to go Monarchy first. While you may want to consider "
"building Ħal Saflieni Hypogeum in your capital city and also building the "
"Pyramids as fast as possible you may want to focus instead on maxing science "
"and using scientists for getting Monarchy really fast. In this case you may "
"want to build the Pyramids after revolting and switching to Monarchy or "
"maybe even Fudamentalism. Then again Despotism may be great if you need to "
"defend. It allows a crazy number of units to be used for keeping the people "
"content. This together with Pyramids is also great."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:224
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Your centers of government (cities with Palace and 2nd Palace) get a +50% "
"bonus to gold production.\n"
"* Celebrating cities produce one extra trade point for every tile which is "
"already producing trade. (Cities below size 3 will not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 3 units for free (the maximum possible). "
"Further units each cost 1 gold per turn.\n"
"* Each city tolerates up to 3 aggressively deployed military units. Each "
"further unit causes 1 unhappy citizen.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 3 military units inside a city "
"will each force 1 unhappy citizen to become content.\n"
"* Base corruption is 10%. This increases with distance from the capital "
"(half as fast with knowledge of The Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 10%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  The number of units avoiding the military unhappiness will also "
"double at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Ihre Hauptstadt erhält einen Bonus von 50% auf ihre Goldproduktion.\n"
"• Feiernde Städte erzeugen einen extra Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, welches "
"bereits Handel erzeugt (Städte kleiner 3 werden nicht feiern).\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu drei Einheiten umsonst unterstützen; jede weitere "
"Einheit kostet ein Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert bis zu 3 aggressiv eingesetzte Militäreinheiten, jede "
"weitere verursacht einen unzufriedenen Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 10% und erhöht sich mit der Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt (ab Entdeckung der Firma nur noch halb so schnell).\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 20% und wächst mit "
"zunehmender Entfernung von der Hauptstadt (ab Entdeckung des Handels nur "
"noch halb so schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:242
msgid ""
"Playing with Monarchy? \n"
"Monarchy is great for those players who want to play war. You do not get "
"that much gold of production with Monarchy but instead it is reasonably good "
"for those players who want to attack, attack, and attack. In the late early "
"game and early mid game it is a good alternative also for those who wish to "
"build and not fight wars. Switching to Monarchy will remove the -1 penalty "
"you get from Anarchy, Despotism, and Tribalism and this will allow you to "
"ramp up your economy for the better governments to come. If you go for "
"Monarchy in the early game try to do it fast. Maybe using the scientists for "
"few turns and then getting the tech by T15 - T20. However, even the farmers "
"may want to stick with Monarchy for some time because of the great unit "
"upkeep for workers and less waste."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:275
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* City improvements which would normally have an upkeep of 1 gold are free "
"of upkeep.\n"
"* Each city can support up to 3 units for free (the maximum possible). "
"Further units each cost 1 shield per turn.\n"
"* Each city tolerates up to 3 aggressively deployed military units. Each "
"further unit causes 1 unhappy citizen.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 3 military units inside a city "
"will each force 2 unhappy citizens to become content (the maximum "
"possible).\n"
"* Base corruption is 30%, but is not affected by distance to the capital.\n"
"* There is no production waste.\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  The number of units avoiding the military unhappiness will also "
"double at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Stadtverbesserungen, die sonst ein Gold Unterhalt erfordern, benötigen "
"keinen Unterhalt.\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu drei Einheiten umsonst unterstützen, jede weitere "
"Einheit kostet ein Schild pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert bis zu drei aggressiv eingesetzte Militäreinheiten, "
"jede weitere verursacht einen unzufriedenen Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 30%, ist aber unabhängig von der Entfernung "
"zur Hauptstadt.\n"
"• Es gibt keinerlei Verschwendung in der Produktion."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:290
msgid ""
"Playing with Communism? \n"
"Communistic nations are able to grow big, fast and they can have huge "
"production. The downside is that the gold production is low. If you manage "
"to get the Statue of Liberty it may make sense to switch to Communism really "
"fast. Also, if you have a vast empire and you are allied with someone who "
"has better techs, you may want to play as the commie leader."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:328
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Base science production is 40% that of other governments. (A "
"Fundamentalist city with a Library produces roughly as much science as a "
"city under another government does alone.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 2 "
"gold per turn (except for Fanatics).\n"
"* Each city tolerates up to 2 aggressively deployed military units. Each "
"further unit causes 1 unhappy citizen.\n"
"* Base corruption is 15%. This increases with distance from the capital "
"(half as fast with knowledge of The Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 15%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  The number of units avoiding the military unhappiness will also "
"double at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Der wissenschaftliche Fortschritt ist gegenüber anderen Regierungsformen "
"halbiert.\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu zwei Einheiten umsonst unterstützen, jede weitere "
"Einheit — außer Fanatikern — kostet 2 Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert bis zu zwei aggressiv eingesetzte Militäreinheiten, "
"jede weitere verursacht einen unzufriedenen Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 15% und erhöht sich mit der Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt (ab Kenntnis der Firma nur noch halb so schnell)\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 15% nimmt mit der "
"Entfernung von der Hauptstadt zu (ab Kenntnis des Handels nur noch halb so "
"schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:343
msgid ""
"Playing with fundamentalism? \n"
"Fundamentalism is for a player who needs to build lots funda specific units "
"(Crusaders, Fanatics) fast. This may be useful if you are defending your "
"nation or buying some time to your ally while that other nation needs to "
"focus on something else. Funda can also be used as an alternative early "
"government if you need to get lots of gold fast. With the happiness "
"buildings Funda is like a money printing machine. Choosing this government "
"also makes sense if you plan to steal your techs while fosusing on building "
"infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:371
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Each city gets 2 extra luxury good points.\n"
"* Celebrating cities produce one extra trade point for every tile which is "
"already producing trade. (Cities below size 3 will not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 2 "
"gold per turn.\n"
"* Each city tolerates up to 2 aggressively deployed military units. Each "
"further unit causes 1 unhappy citizen.\n"
"* There is no base level of corruption, but an increasing amount with "
"distance from the capital (half as much as with most other governments). "
"Knowledge of The Corporation eliminates this corruption.\n"
"* Base production waste is 30%, but is not affected by distance to the "
"capital.\n"
"* Has a senate that may prevent declaration of war.\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  The number of units avoiding the military unhappiness will also "
"double at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Feiernde Städte erzeugen einen extra Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, welches "
"bereits Handel erzeugt (Städte kleiner 3 werden nicht feiern).\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann bis zu zwei Einheiten umsonst unterstützen, jede weitere "
"Einheit kostet zwei Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert bis zu zwei aggressiv eingesetzte Militäreinheiten, "
"jede weitere Einheit verursacht einen unzufriedenen Bürger.\n"
"• Es gibt keine Grundkorruption, aber mit zunehmender Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt ensteht solche. Im Verhältnis zu anderen Regierungsformen beträgt "
"diese Steigerung aber nur die Hälfte des Üblichen, mit Kenntnis der Firma "
"wird sie vollständig beseitigt.\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 30%, ist aber unabhängig "
"von der Entfernung zur Hauptstadt."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:388
msgid ""
"Playing with federation? \n"
"Federation may work as a boost for switching into Democracy. If you need to "
"research reasonably fast and there is less need for gold, it may make sense "
"to switch to Federation before you choose another form of govermnent. With "
"Federation you get a nice boost for your science while you are still able to "
"fight wars. However there is a catch to this. You may want to carefully "
"compare your advance to the nations with the other form of government. While "
"Federation receives a generous boost to science, in addition to other "
"bonuses, in the long term it will not be able to compete against "
"Democracies. This of course depends on the game you are playing but "
"typically 20 - 30 turns with Federation should be more than enough in the "
"mid game. After that you may want to quit fighting wars and focus on "
"something else or maybe switch to another government."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:421
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Cities produce an extra trade point for every worked land tile that is "
"already producing trade.\n"
"* Celebrating cities produce a further trade point for every worked tile "
"(land or water) which is already producing trade. (Cities below size 3 will "
"not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support one unit for free. further units each cost 1 shield "
"per turn.\n"
"* Each city tolerates a single aggressively deployed military unit. Each "
"further unit causes 1 unhappy citizen.\n"
"* Base corruption is 25%. This increases with distance from the capital "
"(half as fast with knowledge of The Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 20%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  The number of units avoiding the military unhappiness will also "
"double at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Städte erzeugen einen extra Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, das bereits "
"Handel erzeugt.\n"
"• Feiernde Städte erzeugen einen weiteren Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, das "
"bereits Handel erzeugt (Land oder Wasser; Städte kleiner 3 werden nicht "
"feiern).\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann eine Einheit umsonst unterstützen, jede weitere kostet "
"zwei Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert eine aggressiv eingsetzte Militäreinheit, jede "
"weitere verursacht zwei unzufriedene Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 5% und nimmt mit der Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt zu (ab Kenntnis der Firma nur noch halb so schnell).\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 25% und nimmt mit der "
"Entfernung von der Hauptstadt zu (ab Kenntnis des Handels nur noch halb so "
"schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:438
msgid ""
"Playing with Republic? \n"
"Republic is the fast lane to Democracy and it is quite bad if you plan to "
"fight wars. Unlike with some other governments you can declare wars while in "
"Republic. This however comes with a hefty price unless you manage to keep "
"the wars extremely short or you crush a very weak enemy. Republics can "
"succeed if you have a very low number of units and you can afford to focus "
"on building Markets, Mercantile Exchanges, and Banks instead of military "
"units and huge numbers of workers. One of the best ways to succeed with a "
"Republic is to make peace or alliance with everyone around you and then "
"focus on ramping up your economy. Republic may also work better if your "
"cities have overlapping tiles. If you have little space for your empire it "
"may make sense to micromanage the worked tiles as Republic as your "
"government. This will allow you to reduce the number of workers since "
"overlapping city improvements will make it possible to use the same improved "
"tile for two or more cities. For example, when one city is about to grow "
"(currently getting +3 food) and needs +2 food you may switch a grassland "
"tile (irrigated, resource +1 production, and roads) to another city and use "
"a regular plans tile (irrigated, with roads) for the city only needing +2 "
"food. This way you do not produce +1 extra food going to waste and the other "
"city will benefit from the same worker tile. Like always there are many ways "
"to deal with the governments and another way to look at this is saying that "
"in Republic you can afford more buildings, while in Monarchy you can afford "
"more units. Going from Monarchy to Democracy is a popular route even while "
"in some situations adding Fedetation between them might make sense."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:480
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"* Cities produce an extra trade point for every worked land tile that is "
"already producing trade.\n"
"* Celebrating cities produce a further trade point for every worked tile "
"(land or water) which is already producing trade. (Cities below size 3 will "
"not celebrate.)\n"
"* Each city can support one unit for free. Further units each cost 2 gold "
"per turn.\n"
"* Each city tolerates a single aggressively deployed military unit. Each "
"further unit causes 2 unhappy citizens.\n"
"* Base corruption is 5%. This increases with distance from the capital (half "
"as fast with knowledge of The Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 25%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade).\n"
"* Has a senate that may prevent declaration of war.\n"
"* Big cities with size of 9 or more will get an extra 50 % defense against "
"military attacks. \n"
"* The number of free units will be doubled for cities with size of 9 or "
"more.  Unlike with other governments, the number of units avoiding the "
"military unhappiness will NOT be doubled at this size."
msgstr ""
"• Städte erzeugen einen extra Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, das bereits "
"Handel erzeugt.\n"
"• Feiernde Städte erzeugen einen weiteren Handelspunkt für jedes Feld, das "
"bereits Handel erzeugt (Land oder Wasser; Städte kleiner 3 werden nicht "
"feiern).\n"
"• Jede Stadt kann eine Einheit umsonst unterstützen, jede weitere kostet "
"zwei Gold pro Runde.\n"
"• Jede Stadt toleriert eine aggressiv eingsetzte Militäreinheit, jede "
"weitere verursacht zwei unzufriedene Bürger.\n"
"• Die Grundkorruption beträgt 5% und nimmt mit der Entfernung von der "
"Hauptstadt zu (ab Kenntnis der Firma nur noch halb so schnell).\n"
"• Die Grundverschwendung in der Produktion beträgt 25% und nimmt mit der "
"Entfernung von der Hauptstadt zu (ab Kenntnis des Handels nur noch halb so "
"schnell)."

#: data/royale/governments.ruleset:498
#, c-format
msgid ""
"Playing with Democracy? \n"
"Playing with a Democracy is probably the most effective way of creating a "
"super power, but this comes with a price. Unlike with some other setups "
"Democracies are quite vulnerable while the player is ramping up the economy. "
"The most common reason to have Democracy as your form of goverment is to "
"build an extremely powerful economy that will simply crush those nations "
"daring to act against your happy Democracy with you as its eternal leader. "
"If you are not planning to fight wars and you can afford to build Markets "
"and other trade related buildings, Democracy is probably the best choice you "
"can make. With Democracy you will get the best possible effect for compound "
"interest and if you manage to make your cities to celebrate this effect is "
"even more powerful. Democracies are able to maintain a decent army and lots "
"of workers. One very powerful strategy for you to consider is to switch "
"between max tax and max sci. If you are confident enough you may want to "
"delay scientific advance and focus on max taxing so that your economy will "
"grow really fast. There is however a catch to this. If you postpone "
"researching too much your enemy may be able to surprise you and your "
"outdated army. With a democatic nation it is also extremely important to "
"keep your citizens not only content but happy and celebrating. Celebration "
"gives you +1 extra trade for each tile already producing trade if you manage "
"to keep your cities celebrating. On some other setups using more than "
"20% luxury is usually considered bad but with Royale's trade building setup "
"it may be worth celebrating even with +40% luxury. It all depends on the "
"situiation, but it may be worth it if you manage to avoid building some "
"happiness buildings on the new cities while focusing the resources on the "
"big and old cities producing most of your gold. Also, if you are attacked or "
"need to fight wars it may make sense to home some units on the low "
"production cities. That way if those units cause unhappiness they will do it "
"for those cities that matter less to you. "
msgstr ""

